{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The top words analysis revealed a disproportionate representation of certain words in content from generative AI.",
    "This overrepresentation could stem from biases present in the training data, including stereotypes, which the models further amplified by reinforcing associations among word tokens (Liang et al. 2021).",
    "However, human experts display much less positive tones and emotions, which could be due to the emotional numbness (i.e., significantly lower emotional reactions to hedonic experiences) of experts (Rocklage, Rucker and Nordgren 2021).",
    "Another possible explanation could be the strategies used by developers to fine-tune generative AI models that aim to improve their interactions with humans, as evidenced by the more positive emotions and tones.",
    "Although automatic text analysis tools can identify differences between reviews from human experts and generative AI, can humans perceive those differences without relying on extensive vocabulary dictionaries and quantitative algorithms?"
  ],
